==English==
===Pronunciation===
*SAMPA: /"naU@%deIz/
===Adverb===

#In these days; at the present time.
#: ''Work that was once done by hands is often done by machine nowadays.''

===Quotations=== <!-- More exact dates, etc.? Neither seems to have found its way onto the web outside online dictionaries -->
: '''Late 1300's:''' ''Wit that men have now a days''  &mdash; Geoffrey Chaucer
: '''Late 1700's:''' ''What men of spirit, nowadays, Come to give sober judgment of new plays?''  &mdash; David Garrick.

